<TITLE> 8 steel millers hurt in explosion </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Narayanganj, June 9 (bdnews24.com)  Eight workers of a steel mill under Fatulla upazila in Narayanganj were injured in a blast furnace explosion on Wednesday. The incident occurred at the Rajdhani Casting Mill at Alikadam of the upazila early Wednesday when liquefied iron splashed on them due to the explosion. Sheikh Shahid, 40, 'Alamgir', 22, 'Sabuj', 20, 'Bakul', 25, and Md Shahid Hossain, 35, were sent to the burn unit of the Dhaka Medical College Hospital with serious injuries. The others could not be identified immediately. They were taking treatment locally. Fatulla Model Police Station officer in charge Jiban Kanti Sarkar told bdnews24.com that the furnace (locally known as bhatti) of Rajdhani Casting Mill, an affiliate of Nabi Steel Mills, exploded with a loud bang. The walls of both sides of the mill collapsed and the tin shed roof flew off. "Eight workers were injured," said the police officer. bdnews24.
